   "source": [
    "# Suffix Array and Suffix Tree
",
    "
",
    "## 1. Suffix Array
",
    "A Suffix Array is a sorted array of all suffixes of a given string. It is a space-efficient alternative to Suffix Trees.
",
    "
",
    "### Key Concepts:
",
    "- **Construction**: Can be built in $O(N \log N)$ or $O(N)$ time.
",
    "- **LCP Array**: Longest Common Prefix array, often used alongside Suffix Array to speed up queries.
",
    "
",
    "### Applications:
",
    "- Pattern matching in $O(M \log N)$.
",
    "- Finding the longest repeated substring.
",
    "- Finding the number of distinct substrings.
",
    "
",
    "---
",
    "
",
    "## 2. Suffix Tree
",
    "A Suffix Tree is a compressed trie containing all the suffixes of a given string.
",
    "
",
    "### Key Features:
",
    "- **Construction**: $O(N)$ time using Ukkonen's algorithm.
",
    "- **Space**: $O(N)$ but with a larger constant factor than Suffix Array.
",
    "
",
    "### Applications:
",
    "- Exact string matching.
",
    "- Finding the longest common substring of two strings.
",
    "- Palindrome finding."
   ]
  }
 ],
